snippet.textDisplay:
First of all, if every song has a different music director, what's Strings there for? Just to take all the credits or just to fill their pockets by being the producer?

Secondly, what's up with Momina's voice, are they using auto-tune? Whatever it is, i did not like it. I didn't think i would ever say something like this about Coke Studio but i don't know. Nothing seems right. What's the point in even inviting her to Coke Studio? Because she has a pretty face? I'm sorry but I don't think she deserved a chance in CS, while excellent singers like Falak Shabir, Bilal Saeed still haven't gotten the chance to perform in CS. This sucks. I think we need Rohail Hayat back. I hope i'm not the only one who's missing him.

And last but not least, this song has proved that no one can even come close to singing, when it's about re-singing a song of the greatest, Nusrat Fateh Ali Khan.!
snippet.textOriginal:
First of all, if every song has a different music director, what's Strings there for? Just to take all the credits or just to fill their pockets by being the producer?

Secondly, what's up with Momina's voice, are they using auto-tune? Whatever it is, i did not like it. I didn't think i would ever say something like this about Coke Studio but i don't know. Nothing seems right. What's the point in even inviting her to Coke Studio? Because she has a pretty face? I'm sorry but I don't think she deserved a chance in CS, while excellent singers like Falak Shabir, Bilal Saeed still haven't gotten the chance to perform in CS. This sucks. I think we need Rohail Hayat back. I hope i'm not the only one who's missing him.

And last but not least, this song has proved that no one can even come close to singing, when it's about re-singing a song of the greatest, Nusrat Fateh Ali Khan.!
